    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - SPLASH SHIELDS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SPLASH SHIELDS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Shields - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean dirt and debris away from all splash shield mount hardware.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901113" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901113.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Right Splash Shield</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RIGHT SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RIGHT FRONT FENDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove five bolts and right splash shield from front fender.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901114" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901114.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Left Splash Shield</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT FRONT FENDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEFT SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four bolts and left splash shield from front fender.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901115" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901115.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Splash Shield Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ATTACHMENT PINS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. INSULATION PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RIGHT SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PUSH PINS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RUBBER PANELS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To disassemble the splash shields, remove the push pins and rubber panels from the
                    splash shields.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the attachment pins and insulation panel from the right splash shield.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Shields - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the insulation panel on the right splash shield and secure with the attachment
                    pins (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901115">Figure 17, Items 2, 3, and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align rubber panels on splash shields and secure with push pins (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901115">Figure 17, Items 5 and 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install left splash shield on left side of hood and secure with four bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901114">Figure 16</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 15 to 19 lbf-ft (20 to 26 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install right splash shield on right side of hood and secure with five bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901113">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 15 to 19 lbf-ft (20 to 26 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
